{
  "stem": "22883.1",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Apparently her mother, she was a nanny at the Graf [INAUDIBLE] family, and she was nursing [INAUDIBLE] daughter, which was born at the same time when my mother was born.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So her mother was the nanny of that family.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Another family in [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It was the center of Poland not far away from Lublin.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "You asked me first what-- how the life was.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "OK.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Also quite interesting to live with the people who didn't belong to the same culture, or to the same milieu.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Customs, and so on.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "They had different customs.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Those [INAUDIBLE] people.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "We called them [INAUDIBLE] and-- And of course because they were farmers, quite poor [? hop ?] farmers.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "So it was much different than-- than our life.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "This school teacher's family life.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My childhood was quite not very pleasant, because, unfortunately, my father was despotic type and very demanding.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And so we lived-- lived all the time in a certain state of fright, I would say.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We had no-- we could not be individual or to do what we wanted.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I think it's-- well, apparently it lasted until the war-- the war started.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I remember in 1939, my father came and said, boys, get up.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We are going away from Warsaw.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Because we lived 16 kilometers from Warsaw-- so a suburb of Warsaw-- and he came in saying, boys-- to-- to myself and my brother-- we are going away because the-- on the radio they were calling to-- that all male people, population, should leave and go east, because the Germans are coming.",
      "word_count": 52
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So without any questions asking or what, we just went out.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
